<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAVID DUKE'S STRONG SHOWING IN LOUISIANA VOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Much Too Close for Comfort" (editorial, Oct. 11): 
</P>
<P>
The best thing that can be said about Louisiana's primary is not that Duke 
lost, but that hopefully it sends a message to our self-serving politicians 
that the electorate is becoming fed up with candidates whose positions depend 
solely upon which special-interest group they are speaking to at the time. Like 
it or not, at least we know exactly where Duke stands. 
</P>
<P>
And the demagogue who arises in California won't claim that the government sold 
the state to the immigrants; he will claim, justifiably, that the politicians 
gave it to them. 
</P>
<P>
TRENT DAVOL SANDERS 
</P>
<P>
Angeles National Forest 
</P>
</TEXT>
