<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY: SARDUCCI'S GOOD FOR OPENERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AMY McCURDY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sarducci's Cafe and Grill is best known for its Italian dishes and seafood, and 
features what the restaurant touts as "South Orange County's Most Incredible 
Desserts." But what many don't realize is how good the breakfasts are. 
</P>
<P>
In keeping with the nature of San Juan Capistrano, Sarducci's offers a very 
relaxed environment and good, friendly service. The place is adorned with 
ceiling fans and white patio furniture and provides a choice of seating indoors 
or out. If you choose to sit out on the lower patio, you can watch the morning 
trains come in. The best news is that it's one of those rare places where you 
can get quality food and generous portions at a very reasonable price. 
</P>
<P>
Definitely worth trying are the Eggs Alaska (poached egg on an English muffin 
with tomatoes, crab and Hollandaise sauce), and the Seafood Omelette, with 
crab, shrimp and Hollandaise. The Italian Sausage Omelette is topped with tangy 
marinara sauce and comes, as all omelets here do, with potatoes and mini-carrot 
muffins or toast. 
</P>
<P>
The Cajun breakfast, with spicy smoked ham, sausage, chicken and scrambled 
eggs, pleases the more adventurous palate. Other good possibilities include 
chicken and mushroom crepes with sherried cream sauce, seafood crepes with 
crab, shrimp and Hollandaise sauce, and a familiar favorite: eggs Benedict. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to their good coffee, Sarducci's offers espresso or cappuccino, and 
a choice of fresh juices. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday brunches, accompanied by champagne, fruit juice or mimosa, are $7.95. 
The regular breakfasts are moderately priced, at around $10 to $12 for two 
people. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
 Sarducci's, 31751 Camino Capistrano, San Juan Capistrano. Open daily, 8 a.m. 
to 10 p.m., Friday and Saturday till 11 p.m. (714) 493-9593. AMY McCURDY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, In keeping with Capistrano. HENRY DIROCCO / For The Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
