<TEXT>
<P>
Pacific Gas &amp; Electric Co.: Third-quarter earnings for the San 
Francisco-based utility were $394.2 million, up 24% over the same quarter of 
1989. Revenue was $2.6 billion, up 17% over the third quarter of last year. The 
company said the results were due to an "excellent performance" by the utility 
business and its Diablo Canyon nuclear power plant. 
</P>
