<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLIPBOARD; 
</P>
<P>
DRESS FOR SUCCESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Researched by: DALLAS M. JACKSON / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shopping for Halloween costumes at a thrift shop can be an adventure. For the 
most part it is the luck of the draw because recycled clothing comes in and 
goes out in a matter of days. But with a little imagination, an innovative 
costume can be put together faster than you can say "abracadabra" and for less 
than the retail cost of bat wings and lizard lips. 
</P>
<P>
Here's a list of places where you can strike a costume bargain: 
</P>
<P>
ASSISTANCE LEAGUE OF TUSTIN 
</P>
<P>
445 El Camino Real, Tustin 
</P>
<P>
(714) 544-2612 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 1 to 3:30 p.m. Monday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $1 and up 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Mostly items for women and children. There are a few masks 
and hats, Batman costumes and clothes that can be turned into costumes. 
</P>
<P>
BARGAIN BOX 
</P>
<P>
(ASSISTANCE LEAGUE OF HUNTINGTON BEACH) 
</P>
<P>
16582 Gothard St., Huntington Beach 
</P>
<P>
(714) 847-6511 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 10:30 a.m. to 3:30 p.m. Tuesday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $2 to $20 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and children. Ethnic costumes, Madonna, 
Elvira, mermaid, Count Dracula and old-fashioned dresses (Staff can assist in 
putting together a costume). 
</P>
<P>
BETWEEN FRIENDS 
</P>
<P>
140 E. Main St., Tustin 
</P>
<P>
(714) 838-6773 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 10:30 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday-Friday; 10:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $5 to $50 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and children. Barmaid, witch, vampire, 
old-fashioned bathing suits for men and women, Raggedy Ann, rock star, military 
wear and hospital greens. The shop also has a catalogue with 100 costumes and 
accessories from which to choose; special orders can be filled in two days. 
</P>
<P>
DISABLED AMERICAN VETERANS THRIFT STORE 
</P>
<P>
9892 Westminster Ave., Garden Grove 
</P>
<P>
(714) 636-2400 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 8:30 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday-Thursday; 8:30 a.m. to 8 p.m. Friday; 8:30 
a.m. to 7 p.m. Saturday; 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $1 to $9 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Costumes for men, women and children. Masks, hats, wigs, 
costume jewelry; witch, rabbit, some ethnic costumes, formals, martial arts and 
military costumes. 
</P>
<P>
JANET LEE SHOPS 
</P>
<P>
2007 S. Main St., Santa Ana 
</P>
<P>
(714) 545-0900 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Monday-Friday; 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $3 to $10 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and children. Fairy princess, clown, 
Sesame Street's Cookie Monster, Dracula and convict costumes. 
</P>
<P>
LUTHERAN SOCIAL SERVICES THRIFT SHOPS 
</P>
<P>
23532 El Toro Road, El Toro 
</P>
<P>
(714) 768-0405 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Monday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $1 to $40 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and a few for children. No commercial 
costumes, though there are period clothes from the 1920s, '30s and '40s as well 
as Asian, doctor and peasant costumes. 
</P>
<P>
LUTHERAN SOCIAL SERVICES THRIFT SHOPS 
</P>
<P>
12900 Main St., Garden Grove 
</P>
<P>
(714) 537-1373 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $2 to $30 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and children. Kimonos, military 
uniforms, French maid complete with bustier and garters, bear costumes, period 
clothing from the 1950s and '60s, and wigs. 
</P>
<P>
NEW DIRECTIONS THRIFT SHOP 
</P>
<P>
600 W. 19th St., Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
(714) 548-9927 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 10 a.m. to 7 p.m. Monday-Thursday; 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Friday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $3 to $12 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men and women. Wigs, period clothing, graduates, 
flappers, military, clown, doctor and nurse costumes. 
</P>
<P>
OLDE'N NEW 
</P>
<P>
145 E. 19th St., Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
(714) 646-1569 
</P>
<P>
Hours: noon to 7 p.m. Tuesday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $2 to $25 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and children. Unusual costumes, wigs, 
noses, hats, handmade exotic, sequined, jeweled masks; bear, clown and rabbit 
costumes. 
</P>
<P>
SALVATION ARMY THRIFT STORE 
</P>
<P>
7138 Westminster Blvd., Westminster 
</P>
<P>
(714) 898-6281 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday-Saturday 
</P>
<P>
Cost: 50 cents to $5 
</P>
<P>
What's available: Items for men, women and children. Mr. Potato Head, Hawaiian, 
pirate and princess costumes; hats, shoes, vests and wigs. (There are nine 
other Salvation Army Thrift Store locations throughout Orange County.) 
</P>
<P>
THRIFT VILLAGE THRIFT STORE 
</P>
<P>
9782 Garden Grove Blvd., Garden Grove 
</P>
<P>
(714) 638-4163 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 9 a.m. to 9 p.m. Monday-Saturday; 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Sunday 
</P>
