<P>
4TH CHESS MATCH GAME ADJOURNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fourth game of the world championship chess match between champion Garry 
Kasparov and challenger Anatoly Karpov was adjourned Wednesday night after 40 
moves. 
</P>
<P>
Play was halted at 10:30 p.m. when Kasparov wrote down his 41st move and sealed 
it in an envelope. 
</P>
<P>
The game is to be resumed this afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Kasparov, with 2 points to Karpov's 1, had the white pieces in the latest game 
of the $3-million world championship match. Game 3 ended in a draw Tuesday 
night. Kasparov won the second game on Oct. 10. The first game, played Oct. 8, 
ended in a draw. 
</P>
<P>
Here are the moves from Wednesday's match: 
</P>
<P>
