<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTRY SINGER NAOMI JUDD TO RETIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Country singer Naomi Judd announced Wednesday in Nashville that she will retire 
early next year for health reasons. The announcement signals the end of the 
Judds, the mother and daughter team that has been one of country music's most 
successful attractions since 1984. 
</P>
<P>
Judd, 44, who was found to have hepatitis 10 months ago, said the retirement 
will come at the end the duo's current "Love Can Build a Bridge" tour. Wynonna, 
her 26-year-old daughter, plans to continue in country music as a solo artist. 
</P>
<P>
The Judds, who have had more than a dozen No. 1 country hits, including "Why 
Not Me" and "Grandpa (Tell Me 'Bout the Good Old Days)," have been honored by 
the Country Music Assn. as the field's best vocal group/duo for the past six 
years. 
</P>
