<P>
HEALTH DEPARTMENT OFFICIAL SAYS SHE WILL LEAVE POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kay C. James is leaving her position as the chief spokeswoman for the Health 
and Human Services Department, she has announced. James, 42, will become chief 
operating officer of the One to One Foundation, which organizes programs that 
provide role models and mentors to troubled youths. 
</P>
