<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a game dominated by big offensive plays, Rodgers' 75-yard interception 
return might have been the most entertaining touchdown in the Marauders' 43-7 
Foothill Conference victory over East Los Angeles on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
The play occurred late in the fourth quarter when Antelope Valley linebacker 
Lester Larry grabbed Oscar Tavera's jersey and spun the quarterback around in 
an effort to sack him. 
</P>
<P>
Tavera tried to dumped the ball off to a teammate but hit the unsuspecting 
Rodgers instead. 
</P>
<P>
Rodgers has played an instrumental role in the Marauders' season -- at 5-0-1 
the team is off to its best start since 1954 -- anchoring a defense that has 
given up 52 points in six games. He has a team-leading 11 sacks and ranks third 
with 38 unassisted and assisted tackles. 
</P>
<P>
Daron Rodgers: Antelope Valley 
</P>
<P>
Football: Defensive end 
</P>
<P>
Freshman: 6-foot-3, 210 pounds 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Daron Rodgers 
</P>
