<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WACKERMAN LIFTS CLU PAST CLAREMONT-MUDD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rachel Wackerman scored two goals to lead Cal Lutheran past Claremont-Mudd, 
3-1, in a women's nonconference soccer match Wednesday at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Wackerman's second goal gave her 25 for the season and she added an assist as 
Cal Lutheran improved to 9-3. Vanessa Martin scored the Regals' other goal, and 
Danielle Deyarmond and Lolita Marquez added assists. 
</P>
<P>
Claremont-Mudd fell to 6-7-2. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE WRESTLING 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 26, Bakersfield 17 -- Former Westlake High standout Neal Mason 
improved to 12-0 with an 8-7 decision over Scott Herndon in the 158-pound match 
for Moorpark, which stands 3-1 overall and 1-0 in Western State Conference 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
BOYS' WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 13, Calabasas 8 -- Steve Barron had 11 goals to pace the Knights 
(5-4) in a nonleague match at Calabasas. Womeen Jun had nine assists and two 
goals for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham d. Monroe, 17-15, 15-6, 15-7 -- Tina Larson had 10 kills and 
Meredith Lewis added nine to lead host Birmingham (8-2, 5-1) in a Mid-Valley 
League match. 
</P>
<P>
Sylmar d. Poly, 15-9, 15-8, 15-6 -- Griselda Vasquez had 21 kills to lead the 
Spartans (9-1, 5-1) in a Pac-8 Conference contest at Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys d. Canoga Park, 15-5, 13-15, 15-1, 15-2 -- April Todd and Tracy Fidell 
each had eight kills to lead the host Wolves (10-0, 7-0) in a Pac-8 Conference 
match. 
</P>
<P>
Royal d. Camarillo, 15-6, 15-5, 15-3 -- Jennifer Hamilton had nine kills and 
four kill blocks, and teammate Chantel Loo had 17 service points with two aces 
for host Royal in the Marmonte League match. 
</P>
<P>
Tracy Pahy added 11 service points and Stacey Kaufmann had 11 digs for Royal 
(10-1, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks CES d. Mid-City, 12-15, 15-6, 15-3 -- Sherman Oaks improved to 5-2 
with the Magnet League win. 
</P>
<P>
Kingdrew d. Valley Alternative, 1-15, 15-3, 15-10 -- Star Whitlow had five 
kills for visiting Valley Alternative (3-4) in a Magnet League match. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale Adventist Academy d. Providence, 15-4, 15-8, 5-15, 8-15, 16-14 -- 
Glendale improved to 8-4 with the nonleague win. 
</P>
