<TEXT>
<P>
Paramount's Books to Be Examined: Superior Court Judge Harvey Schneider said he 
expects to appoint a "special master" to examine Paramount Pictures' books 
before the court sets damages in Art Buchwald's suit over the film "Coming to 
America." 
</P>
<P>
Attorneys for both sides said they would accept Franklin Johnson, an 
entertainment expert with the Price Waterhouse accounting firm, as the court's 
independent expert. Schneider asked the attorneys to schedule a hearing with 
Johnson in coming weeks to agree on a "game plan" for the examination. 
Schneider has already ruled that the film, starring Eddie Murphy, was based on 
a story by Buchwald, despite Paramount's claims. 
</P>
