SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: IMPERIAL BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arson is suspected in an early-morning fire that caused heat and smoke damage 
to a classroom Wednesday at Mar Vista High School in Imperial Beach, the 
Sheriff's Department arson unit said. 
</P>
<P>
About a dozen firefighters fought the blaze, which started at 2:31 a.m. and was 
contained shortly after 4 a.m., Paul Bledsoe, an arson investigator for the 
