Photo, Heartfelt Message to Troops in Gulf: Students put their thoughts, wishes 
and prayers down on paper, along with whimsical cartoon characters, drawings 
and signatures, in a huge greeting to American soldiers who are now stationed 
in Saudi Arabia. The 60-foot-long banner contains 250 to 300 signatures and 
messages from students and community members. It was created at Flintridge 
Preparatory School in La Canada Flintridge by members of the Key Club, a 
nonprofit service organization that is sponsored by the Kiwanis Club. The club 
has about 45 teen-age members. The banner was sent to New York this week before 
being forwarded to the overseas troops. The notes and signatures on the 
colorful banner surround the central, large message that the club wanted to 
stress to the members of the military: "You're in Our Hearts." RICARDO 
