<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
ARIZONA'S MALAUULU IN HOSPITAL BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arizona quarterback George Malauulu was hospitalized for several hours Tuesday, 
only days after Billy Johnson, a running back, was on life support at a local 
hospital, Coach Dick Tomey said. 
</P>
<P>
Malauulu, a sophomore from Carson, collapsed in the dressing room after 
practice and was taken to the University of Arizona Medical Center, where his 
condition was diagnosed as dehydration. 
</P>
<P>
He was released. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, a redshirt freshman from San Jose, collapsed Friday before the 
Wildcats left for a road trip to Oregon State. 
</P>
<P>
He was hospitalized through the weekend for treatment of a case diagnosed as 
bronchitis. 
</P>
<P>
Tomey said Johnson's condition has improved but added that the back probably 
will miss the team's next five games. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona is 4-2 coming off a 35-21 loss to Oregon State last Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
