<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
COLTS ARE EXPECTED TO START DICKERSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eric Dickerson was activated by the Indianapolis Colts for Sunday's game in 
Denver against the Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, who has missed the first five games of the season on the club's 
non-football injured list, is expected to start. 
</P>
<P>
He needs only 11 yards in that game to move past O.J. Simpson into sixth place 
on the NFL all-time rushing list. 
</P>
<P>
The Colts also signed veteran quarterback Joe Ferguson to a one-year contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
