<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAIDERS; 
</P>
<P>
BELL UNCONCERNED BY BO'S ARRIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Running back Greg Bell said he's not worried about Bo Jackson's arrival, even 
if it does figure to cut into his playing time. 
</P>
<P>
"For some reason, people forget that I piled up a lot of yards over the last 
two years," he said. 
</P>
<P>
"So why would I be concerned with that?" 
</P>
<P>
Bell is out with a right ankle sprain suffered in Sunday's 24-17 victory over 
the Seattle Seahawks. He is listed as doubtful for Sunday's game against the 
San Diego Chargers. Raider Coach Art Shell said Bell may be placed on injured 
reserve. 
</P>
<P>
Defensive end Howie Long and offensive tackle Bruce Wilkerson returned to 
practice. Long was on injured reserve since Week 2 with a broken right foot. 
Wilkerson has been out all season with a knee injury. Shell said he will wait a 
few days before making a decision whether Long will play against San Diego. 
CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES RAIDERS (FOOTBALL TEAM); FOOTBALL PLAYERS; BELL, GREG; LONG, HOWIE; 
SPORTS INJURIES 
