<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The judge who took himself off Howard Spira's attempted extortion case because 
he knew George Steinbrenner, the alleged victim, has been assigned to a 
different case in the baseball controversy. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. District Judge John E. Sprizzo has been assigned to Steinbrenner's lawsuit 
against the company that transcribed statements during Commissioner Fay 
Vincent's probe of the New York Yankee owner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
