DRIVE-BY SHOOTING WOUNDS YOUTH, 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 15-year-old Oxnard boy was struck in the arm by a bullet Wednesday afternoon 
in a drive-by shooting on Campbell Way, a city police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose name was not released, was fired upon at 3:10 p.m. by one of 
three occupants in a passing car. He was treated for the gunshot wound to his 
right arm at St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard police officials said they are uncertain whether it was a gang-related 
shooting. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
