<HEADLINE>
<P>
OIL RECYCLING TO BE EXPANDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A used-oil recycling program in Thousand Oaks that has collected more than 
10,000 gallons in nine months will be expanded. 
</P>
<P>
Grahame Watts, the city's recycling coordinator, said the program, which since 
February has collected residual auto fluids free of charge on the third 
Saturday of each month, now will also accept the fluids on the first Thursday 
of each month. 
</P>
<P>
The program allows residents to bring used transmission, crankcase, gearbox and 
differential oil to the city's Municipal Service Center at 1851 De Havilland 
Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The next scheduled collection dates are Saturday from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. and Nov. 
1 from 11 a.m. to 7 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
