<P>
TEEN TO COMPETE AT NATIONAL 4-H EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Agoura 4-H Club member who makes ice cream from goat's milk will represent 
Ventura County at the National 4-H Congress in Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
Amy Albitre, 18, won Southern California regional, state and Western sectional 
contests to qualify for the national competition Dec. 1 to 5. She is a student 
at Pierce College and has been a 4-H member for nine years. 
</P>
<P>
Albitre, the daughter of Sue and Tony Albitre of Agoura, was a Ventura County 
4-H all-star in 1989. She also won awards at this year's Ventura County Fair. 
She plans to be a veterinarian. JACK SEARLES 
