<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: TEMPLE CITY; 
</P>
<P>
INCREASE IN HOME SIZES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Property owners may now build larger two-story houses, the City Council decided 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The living area permitted in a two-story house may now equal 50% of the lot 
size, or 2,500 square feet, whichever is greater. 
</P>
<P>
Previously, the ratio of living area to lot size was 35%, Community Development 
Director Robert Dawson said. 
</P>
<P>
In a related action Tuesday, the council moved to reduce the bulky appearance 
of apartments and condominiums by approving three changes in the Zoning Code. 
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules, second floors will be limited to 75% of the area of first 
floors; each condo or apartment unit must have at least 500 square feet of 
landscaped area, and all units facing streets must have a front rather than 
side appearance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
