<P>
DEVELOPER FOR DOWNTOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has chosen Hopkins Development Co. of Newport Beach to try to 
develop a retail center south of Buffums department store downtown. 
</P>
<P>
The council, acting as the Redevelopment Agency, this week designated Hopkins 
as the developer for a 22-acre site north of Mission Boulevard and east of 
Garey Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, another company, CSA Real Estate Development of Anaheim, tried 
without success to secure major tenants for the same site. 
</P>
<P>
City officials said Hopkins has proposed to build housing, either single-family 
homes or townhouses, on part of the site to improve the project's financial 
feasibility. City officials said they want to keep Buffums, either at its 
current site or in a new retail center downtown. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement gives Hopkins 90 days to secure letters of interest from 
potential tenants and to prepare a development plan. 
