<HEADLINE>
<P>
BANK ROBBERY SUSPECT ARRESTED BY FBI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man wanted in connection with a bank robbery in Cleveland, Ohio, two months 
ago was arrested Wednesday at an apartment complex here, an FBI spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Terrance Gray, 24, was being held in Orange County Jail without bail pending an 
appearance before a U.S. magistrate today on suspicion of bank robbery, FBI 
spokesman Wylie B. Cox said. 
</P>
<P>
Gray was identified as a suspect after a Cleveland TV station broadcast a 
photograph taken during the bank robbery in which $3,591 was taken, Cox said. A 
viewer recognized the photo and contacted the FBI, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove police investigators developed leads on Gray's location in Orange 
County, Cox said, declining to elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
FBI agents arrested Gray as he drove into the parking lot of a Fullerton 
apartment complex, Cox said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
