<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NO. 9 COSTA MESA TOPS LAGUNA HILLS IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Costa Mesa High School, the ninth-ranked water polo team in the county, 
defeated Laguna Hills, 11-9, Wednesday at Laguna Hills and took sole possession 
of first place in the Pacific Coast League. 
</P>
<P>
Corey Delahunt had four goals and Julian Popov had three to lead Costa Mesa 
(11-7, 3-0 in league). 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills is 2-1 in the league. 
</P>
<P>
In Sea View League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 7, Tustin 6 -- Rob Worthing scored his fourth goal with 37 
seconds remaining to give No. 2 Newport Harbor (10-4, 2-1) the victory over 
unranked Tustin (12-6, 1-2). Mike Gonzalez had 17 saves for the host Tillers. 
</P>
<P>
In Empire League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 8, Esperanza 5 -- Matt Szoboda had three goals and Joey Benson had 10 
saves for No. 3 El Dorado (3-0 in league). 
</P>
<P>
In Sunset League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Edison 11, Marina 4 -- Todd McClung had three goals and drew two penalty shots 
for Edison (13-7, 4-0) at Golden West College. 
</P>
<P>
In South Coast League girls' cross-country: 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 22, Mission Viejo 33 -- Jennifer Gillis (18:46) and Kelly Roda (18:47) 
finished together to lead No. 1 Irvine (5-0), to the victory on the three-mile 
course at Laguna Niguel Regional Park. 
</P>
