<P>
SALVADOR GUERRILLA RAID REPELLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN SALVADOR 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The army today drove off leftist guerrillas who attacked air force headquarters 
with homemade mortars and automatic weapons, and authorities said several 
people were wounded. 
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman said he had an initial report that one military mechanic 
was wounded and one aircraft was damaged in the three hours of fighting at 
Ilopango air base on the east side of the capital. 
</P>
