<P>
TV TIP SNARES EX-BUNNY CONVICT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FOND DU LAC, Wis. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The "tabloid TV" notoriety of a former Playboy bunny waitress and policewoman 
convicted of murdering her former husband's ex-wife helped lead to her capture 
three months after she escaped from prison. 
</P>
<P>
Lawrencia (Bambi) Bembenek, 31, was arrested at an apartment in Thunder Bay, 
Ontario, on Wednesday on a tip from a California viewer of last week's episode 
of "America's Most Wanted" who said she had waited on him. 
</P>
<P>
Bembenek, who has steadfastly professed her innocence, was captured with her 
fiance, Dominic Gugliatto, 34. 
</P>
<P>
Her flight had thrilled supporters in Milwaukee -- prompting sales of T-shirts 
that read, "Run, Bambi, Run" -- and was covered on several TV shows, which 
played up the romantic elements of the escape. 
</P>
<P>
Bembenek supporters say she may have been the victim of a frame-up over her 
knowledge of questionable police activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
