<P>
WORLD SERIES TV RATINGS UP 25% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Television ratings for Game 1 of the World Series were up 25% over the first 
game last year. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday night's game between the defending World Series champion Oakland 
Athletics and the Cincinnati Reds got a 20.2 rating and a 32 share, CBS said. 
</P>
<P>
Last year's opener between the A's and the San Francisco Giants on ABC had a 
16.2 rating and a 30 share, one of the lowest ratings for a night game in World 
Series history. The rating is the percentage of the televisions in the United 
States, and the share is the percentage of televisions in use at the time. 
</P>
