<TEXT>
<P>
A federal judge has ordered two pairs of University of Arizona season 
basketball and football tickets to be auctioned next week, and officials 
estimate they could bring as much as $10,000. 
</P>
<P>
Bankruptcy Judge Lawrence Ollason signed an order Oct. 11 that an auction be 
held at 10 a.m. on Oct. 27 to sell the tickets belonging to David Randall 
Jenkins, a real estate syndicator and developer who filed for bankruptcy three 
years ago for himself, JNC Cos. and other partnerships and companies. 
</P>
<P>
The university had opposed the auction, contending it should be allowed to 
control the tickets. 
