<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
JILLIAN FOUGHT ILLNESS WITH HUMOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROCHESTER, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Ann Jillian, who underwent a double mastectomy for breast cancer in 
1985, says humor is a great defense when battling a serious illness. 
</P>
<P>
"A sense of humor as well as faith in God and the support of the ones you love, 
that's what will get you through an experience like that," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Jillian will speak about her experience with cancer Saturday as part of an 
anniversary celebration of Highland Hospital's Breast Care Center. 
</P>
<P>
Jillian, a volunteer for the American Cancer Society, said she isn't shy about 
discussing cancer. 
</P>
<P>
"Cancer isn't a word that should be whispered. It isn't a subject that should 
be hushed up," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
